		<hr size="1">1) Wizards spells have a shorter casting time.<BR>2) Wizards spells hit for more damage.<BR>3) Wizards will have a greater total amount of "hitpoints" in a duel.  (See Force Shield line of spells, there is no comparable line for magicians).</P><P>However some things posted above I'd have to disagree with. </P><P>///mage only has magic based and their pathetic bolts are somewhat fire-based?///</P><P>Magicians have two lines of Direct Damage Spells their top DD is Sun Vortex which is Fire based, which hits for a base of 1550, (Focused Crit is 4030 before PvP subtraction). (Sun Vortex incidently does have a faster casting time than Strike of Ro before focus effects). </P><P>Also I wouldn't waste time rooting the pet in a duel.  In a duel situation a magician should have several charges of instant click dispell magic stocked up for those situations.  (PvP is different than a dual).</P><P>Sure any class can win a duel, a couple of lucky resists and a mage can kill a wizard fast.  But all things being equal the wizard has the upper hand. </P><P>Message edited by: Xymric (7/10/2003 1:31:13 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
