		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=114801">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Lansear Heartrender" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Lansear+Heartrender">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Lansear Heartrender" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1989999&TN=WIZ+vs%2E+MAG%2C++++PvP&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1995169&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Bleh.....</P><P>This is coming from the perspective of a level 65 wiz...level 65 2 days after PoP came out...and has been playing since pre-K.</P><P>For the most part, it was a safe bet that in a mage vs wiz duel, that the easiest way was to root/snare the pet then dd/stun combo the mage until death.</P><P>The advent of the epic pet whom had crazy insane hp and damage output for its day made that a challenge.</P><P>The later coming of the Ward of Xegony and higher pets made that challenge into a life or death situation - ANY pet that quads for 65-70ish, flurrys, has that much hp, casts stuns, (which are fairly resistable), and itself was level 60 or 61 which would play with resistance rates itself...(for those that dont know, Levels > Resistances in terms of resisting a spell...much rather have a three level advantage over something than 15 to a resist), all this combined to make the mage pet in and of itself a seperate duel.</P><P>And lastly, the one that everyone seems to forget...</P><P>With a patch not to long ago, pets we're given the same resistances that their masters had.  Which means that if their masters had 250 MR, that pet ain't getting rooted, excepting maybe the wiz AA root and MAYBE greater decession.  So the challenge changed from rooting a pet and killing a mage to just surviving a level 60 hard as hell hitting, flurry capable stunning pet with a butt load of hp, on top of a mage which is on the side nuking away at his hearts content.  </P><P>Fortunatly, a nice crit on SoS and another smaller nuke or two rids yourself of the pet.</P><P>Now, for those that complain about a mage not nuking as hard as a wizard, your damn right - mages pale in comparison to a wizards DD.  Just because the mages have the potential for 4Kish crits and wizards have the potential for 6Kish crits does NOT mean they are close.  Compare DPS logs and you'll see who nukes more, harder, crits more often, and gets resisted less.  Factor the use of concussion and ancient concussion and you can chain nuke to your hearts content.</P><P>Buuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuut.</P><P>If a mage nukes you for "only" 4K, and he doesn't get a resist, and after pvp changes, thats still a big ass chunk of your hp you've lost.  Yeah, epic skin / force shield can take up a bit of it, but he's still nuking you hard enough that your gonna die in a few seconds.  Plus, after getting the pet dead/down/taken care of, your not gonna have much of a force shield left. </P><P>Anyways, now that I've explained the higher end aspects...</P><P>A few good tactics that I have used to great effect in fighting mages and winning.</P><P>a) Stand CLOSE to them while the pet hits you and use AE's - AE's will damage the pet and the mage.  Not as much as a SoS, but some of the lower end AE's have a nice stun component in them to stop them from casting.</P><P>b) If your dueling outside, get onto a high point and YONDER - the pet will follow, the mage will look for you, and you have some free time to kill the pet before the mage starts to nuke you.</P><P>c) Don't bother with stuns.  They seem like a good idea.  But don't.  (unless your like, 55 or lower....)</P><P>d) Namely, pet first, mage second.  If you do manage to get the AA root on the pet, kill the mage and get out of there - quite often, the pet won't die as long as you hold aggro, even after its master dies, so run run away outta aggro range.</P><P>Will post more later, but I gotta run irl.</P><P>~ Lan<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
